Futon Finder
============

Version 1.0-UNRELEASED

Currently only meant for developers.

Futon Finder is a Chrome Extension that checks the domains you are browsing to
see if there is a running instance of CouchDB on port 5984. For example, if you
are at http://www.example.com then the extension will attempt an AJAX call to
http://www.example.com:5984. If there is a valid response it will pop up a
desktop notification.

Dependencies
------------

jQuery          Used for AJAX and the desktop notification.

jQuery.bbq      Used in the desktop notification for parsing the query string.

